      {
        "id": 1691295,
        "name": "Fred_Daner",
        "username": "F.Daner",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/bbce88/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-20T11:57:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Almost 3 years later and this wine is really now hitting it\u2019s stride. We drank over 2 days and on day one I think this would have fooled most blind. It really reminded me of a top Village level Gevry. Dark and meaty notes with a strong mineral component. It still needs a few hours of air to really shine and show all it\u2019s layers.</p>\n<p>My wife would not share any on day 2 when she came home. This is a silly value at $28. I\u2019ve got a few of the 10 and need to search out some 12\u2019s.</p>\n<p>Cheers</p>",
