        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/bbce88/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-06-20T22:00:29.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Craig- I\u2019d think you\u2019d like this. Would have never thought this was from a riper year. I really would have pegged this a burg blind. Really impressive for the base bottling. I\u2019m going to last my last 2 go a few more years</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"craig v\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n craig v:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks Fred, I\u2019ve only had the 2011 but this producer is on my radar. I\u2019d love to try the 08. Normally, for me, the the big riper years in Oregon like 2002, 2008 and 2012 aren\u2019t my favorites but, in hands of an ultra old school, old vine producer like Eyrie it might be a match made in heaven.  It would be fun to have the 2007 along side the 2008.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>",
